The paper proposes a new learning rate scheduler for deep neural network training, which is a common topic in machine learning and deep learning research. The experiments are conducted on several benchmarks for image classification and LSTM-based activity recognition, indicating that the paper could fit into sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Among these sub-categories, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely ones as they are directly related to the topic of the paper.
